Worst hotel experience ever
Jul 2023 Family
I reserved two rooms well in advance. Two days prior to our arrival I called for adjoining rooms for myself, and my family and was assigned the 2 adjoining room numbers.
But upon arrival we found that the rooms were double booked, and our rooms were given away to the band, that the hotel was full, and it may be doubtful we would even get rooms for the night.
I then spoke to the manager, who said she would try to get us rooms on the same floor if possible, they certainly would not be adjoining as promised. After waiting an hour without room assignments, I told them that we would be leaving, and since we were not given rooms we expected not to be charged.
They charged us for both rooms. After much haggling, including disputing the charges on my card, and putting in a complaint with the Better Business Bureau, I was fully refunded finally after eight weeks.
Im sure if I had not been so persistent, I wouldve been taken advantage of in this way.
As a matter of fact on the day we were to check in, another couple in the reception desk line next to me said that their own promised room was not available and were are put off for four hours.
The couple then told me the same thing happened to them last year, and they swore they would never return. But then relenting, thought they would give Legends another chance.
Never again!

Not a good impression
Aug 2023
First impressions are so important. When I first got there I couldn't check in because their card reader was down and was told to come back in an hour. I did this and still could not check in. The only way to check in was to give them a cash deposit. There was no other way to get to my room. No apology or anything else just give us your money. I had booked and paid in full for my room so you would think they could manually enter my card number for the deposit. The room was clean as was to whole facility. Upon check out I went to get my cash back and again the registration desk couldn't just get me the cash. I had to wait for the next shift to check in which meant I had to wait another 1/2 hour to get my money back. This whole time no one seemed sorry for my having to wait both coming and going. Not a good way to run a business and make people feel they are appreciated

NEVER AGAIN
Jun 2022 Friends
We stayed in the "kids welcome'' hotel on the trip home to Boise. We parked in the valet parking. It was late and we went straight to our room, and it was clean, nice. Cust service was great, and we were comfortable. Early the next morning while daughter and friend were still sleeping (5-6am) my friend and I woke and decided to visit casino for brief chance at our luck. Sometime later, maybe 30 min or less, we were standing at a machine we had just put our $258 winner into when security was suddenly behind us and demands that we come with them immediately. They did not allow us to retrieve our ticket or explain what was happening or what the issue was. We were led to a room and interrogated about where my child was, if I knew who had her, or when I had left her. I knew and answered all of their questions, starting to panic a bit, I demanded they explain what was going on and again we were escorted to another room further down the hall. My 12 yr old daughter sat comfortably in a chair eating a popsicle and jumped up excited to see us. I looked o the staff/security wondering what the the h^*%^ was going on nd was told the following: We seen your daughter in the hallway, and she looked lost. She was unaccompanied and so we recovered her and brought her here. A clerk leaving the shift at 6:30 recognized her so we were able to trace her to your room and subsequently find you. " I inquired as to why my daughter was out of our room and she said she wanted a pop from the machine in the hallway and wondering where we were. My friend in the room was still sleeping as it was now 7:00am. We thanked them for noticing that she was alone- and retrieving us to be reunited. She later told me they never asked her if she wanted to go back to her room or anything else. They just assisted her to the room we were in and gave her a popsicle and told her to wait until our parents got there. We were then told we needed to leave the hotel immediately and would be escorted to retrieve our friend and our belongings, which we were. As we entered the roo the head security lady arrives with the local Yaima Nation Police. We were asked what was happening. After explaining our side, which was brief as we didnt quite understand why they were called there --they asked if they could step inside and make sure there was no weapons etc. I swear the security lady smirked and looked like a starving dog who was thrown a steak. We agreed, they went in with us, woke my friend, looked around and then told the security who was there too- "There is nothing wrong here, there should not have been a problem as far as we can tell it was just as it seemed- the child was headed to the pop machine, and the parents left her sleeping. All is well." They then had a brief discussion and they returned to tell us that we were still being made to leave the property at the casino's request. We got our stuff and were escorted by security (police left) to await our valet. On the way we inquired of our ticket that had been put in the machine that we were not allowed to retrieve. They said," Too bad, it's gone now." and no, they couldn't look at the cameras for us to validate our claim.
They then sent for our car which took like an hour- finally a valet came and told us our key was broke off in the door and it couldn't be started. We asked what now? and they said we would need to call a locksmith to get a key made to start our car. We refused. They offered a ride to a different hotel. We refused, they threatened trespassing, I threatened negligence. They said the key was damaged prior to arriving there, and I disagreed. Regardless, we were not allowed to object without threts. we were given a ride to a friend's house in YAKIMA that we were able to call. They refused to pay for a locksmith or any replacement of ANYthing. We had to pay our own weekend rated locksmith to make a key. When we arrived later that evening (5pmish) there was a tow truck waiting to tow our car. Another half hour and we would have had that nightmare as well.
Do not go here. They are rude, dishonest, bias, judgmental, awful, uncaring staff and thieves all around. WORST experience EVER. I will not return.
